text: Kennedy Katende (born 15 March 1985) is a Swedish amateur boxer from Sundsvall who qualified for the 2008 Olympics in the light-heavyweight division. His second place behind Kenneth Egan was good enough, he benefitted from his compatriot Badou Jack's decision to fight for Gambia.
